We found the hotel's drinks and food were expensive so we had a drink in the bar next door at a fraction of the price, The hotel were so helpful and recommended a good restaurant down the road which did the most amazing tapas as we had a bad experience eating out on our first night.	Our only criticism was the cost of the breakfast (15 Euros, too much when we only wanted a continental breakfast) - we used the cafe Ramplax across the road, excellent value there.	No restaurant but this gives you every reason to explore excellent restaurants literally on your doorstep for evening meals - "pulpo" and "provenza" are opposite and provide great food at great prices.